node.text:
Rotation Workshops Multi-Purpose Hall and Association House | Verson, France | 2022
.
[ACAU Architects / @acau_architectes]
.
The rehabilitation of the former Rotation Workshops was guided by a desire to restore, with respect, this built heritage that reflects the history of the site and the town, in line with the programming desired by the Municipality of Verson (cultural center, multi-purpose hall and association spaces).
.
The proposed project is intended to offer interventions with assertive modernity, always in line with dedicated use. Here, the new generosity of the entrances, the installation of protective canopies, the creation of a courtyard linking the two buildings, the proposal of anodized woodwork with an iridescent tint or the landscaping are all "kindnesses" with the ambition of offering visitors a project that is both functional and poetic.
.
These contemporary interventions, through their writing and materiality, are intended to serve the built heritage and its enhancement within a remarkable landscape. Text description by the architects | Visit www.theradicalproject.com to read more about the project.
.
Source: www.archdaily.com / @archdaily + www.acau-architectes.fr
Photography by:  Charly Broyez / @charly.broyez
.

node.text:
Sacred Places No: 2
Church of San Giovanni Battista
Location: Mogno, Switzerland
Year: 1992-1996
Architect: Mario Botta
⠀
In 1986, an avalanche hit the tiny Swiss village of Mogno, flattening the hamlet’s seventeenth-century church. Architect, Mario Botta, was appointed to design Mogno’s new church and he created a striking, durable, rocky building for the village. He designed it to rise up from the site of the ravaged 17th-century chapel. The contemporary building stands out among the village’s traditional houses because of its cylindrical shape. The end result is a contemporary display of unusual architecture which is especially striking in a region of traditional buildings and homes. In addition to strong and stable products, Botta also wanted to use local materials. The stripy church is clad inside and out in alternating bands of grey Riveo granite and white Peccia marble, both of which are native to the region.
⠀
The church’s angles are striking, the glass circular roof is cut in a diagonal which emphasizes the juxtaposition of glass and stone. The strength of the walls conveys an unmovable force that is balanced by the lightness of the roof’s glass cover. Botta, with his unconventional design, even excluded conventional windows. Rather, the church is illuminated via the glass roof.
⠀

node.text:
I love Japanese traditional streets. It's not easy to preserve old things, so I'm grateful that many people doing their best to preserve them. 
古い街並みが好きです✨古いものを保存するのは簡単ではありません。日本の伝統的なものを今まで代々、大切にくださっている方々に感謝の気持ちでいっぱいです。

1. Narai-juku in Nagano / 奈良井宿（長野県）
2. Tsumago-juku in Nagano / 妻籠宿（長野県）
3. Seki-juku in Mie / 関宿（三重県）
4. Higashi Chaya District in Ishikawa / ひがし茶屋街（石川県）
5. Nagamachi Samurai District  in Ishikawa /  長町武家屋敷跡（石川県）
6.  Mitarai Preservation Distric in Hiroshima / 御手洗町並み保存地区 （広島県）
7. Kakunodate in Akita / 角館（秋田県）
8. Saiko Temple in Shodo Island, Kagawa / 小豆島 西光寺（香川県）
9. Sanmachi Historical Houses Preserved Area in Takayama, Gifu / 高山市 三町伝統的建造物群保存地区（岐阜県）
10. Yanaka Lane in Gujo, Gifu / 郡上市のやなか水のこみち（岐阜県）

京都府、大原
大原は、かつて山城国愛宕群に属し、古くは小原（おはら）とも記されていました。良質の薪炭を生産する“炭焼きの里”としても知られたそうです。
大原という地名が見られるようになるのは、平安期。835年、最澄の弟子・円仁が開山した大原寺（勝林院と来迎院の総称）に由来するとされます。比叡山・延暦寺のふもとにあることから、勝林院・来迎院や、三千院、寂光院など天台宗の寺院が点在。風格ある寺院と四季折々の自然が織りなす景色は趣深く、貴人や文人が都を離れ、ひっそりと暮らす地として選ばれた山里でした。
📍Ohara,Kyoto prefecture,Japan

🗾Google Map : http://bit.ly/3c3yiip

node.text:
This is Hisamatsu a steak and teppanyaki restaurant located in Gifu City in Gifu’s Yahachicho district. I took this photo while staying in the city during my Nakasendō walk. The restaurant has been said to have been in business for more than 30 years. According to a review in the website tabelog.com, the neighborhood is said to have been a lively entertainment district until after the bubble economy of the late 1980’s. This restaurant has managed to hang on as the neighborhood around it has declined. It appears that an older couple are running the restaurant and that their son is working with them and apparently will take over the restaurant. It seems that the house special is the chef’s choice, which is called the “omakase course” (おまかせコース) for between 3,400 and 4,300 yen.

node.text:
石川県、穴水町大竜寺

1598年当初は穴水町川尻（旧南北村地内）に創建しましたが、3世とうてん和尚の時代に、神仏の加護を受けて現在地の中居南に移転し堂宇を再建しました。 とうてん和尚には幾つもの不思議な伝説が残っています。例えば、授戒を懇願してきた娘にとうてん和尚が戒を授けると、水足(みた)しの池を残し、龍の姿に変じて黒雲に乗り、奥津比咩命（おきつひめのみこと）のお使いとして昇天していきました。この伝説をもとに大竜寺と名付けられました。

この能登中居地区は、かつて鋳物で栄えた場所。ここには、9つの寺院や神社を繋ぐ山道を縫うように続く石畳の道の散策コースがあり、これが「さとりの道」と呼ばれており、ゆっくりと見て回ると約1時間ほどかかります。

📍Dairyuji,Ishikawa prefecture,Japan

🗾Google Map : https://bit.ly/2JNGXcV

node.text:
-
L I Q U O R S 🌃
-
People tend to ask 'are you rather a street or an outdoors photographer?' what I can only answer with ‚I’m a photographer.‘

I lately witnessed more and more creators experimenting outside their ordinary niche they were known more on social media & I can honestly only recommend that to everyone since you’ll learn always something new that can be applied to every kind of genre.  To give you the point that stands out to me personally the most: thanks to street photography, I became mostly independent from the conditions under which I’m creating outdoor stuff, while my outdoor photography helped me to focus on more minimalistic frames by removing clutter - one of my biggest issues in the past.  So: get out of your comfort zone, start experimenting & take all experiences as the ultimate fuel for becoming the best creative version of yourself. 🖤
-
Photo from my online gallery 'INSOMNIA‘ - Link in bio! 🌐
-
